1
00:02:00,640 --> 00:02:01,719
You know, this Xiaofang,

2
00:02:01,819 --> 00:02:02,780
she's really got guts.

3
00:02:03,340 --> 00:02:04,280
Two grown men

4
00:02:05,040 --> 00:02:06,760
couldn't slaughter a pig all day.

5
00:02:07,260 --> 00:02:08,780
She did it in one clean stab!

6
00:02:09,400 --> 00:02:09,800
Don't move.

7
00:02:09,860 --> 00:02:10,319
Don't move, don't move.

8
00:02:19,919 --> 00:02:21,379
Xiaofang is pregnant.

9
00:02:21,699 --> 00:02:22,819
Isn't seeing blood

10
00:02:22,840 --> 00:02:23,340
kind of bad for her?

11
00:02:24,979 --> 00:02:25,860
What's bad about it?

12
00:02:26,319 --> 00:02:27,319
I think it's great.

13
00:02:27,520 --> 00:02:28,860
The kid will definitely be brave.

14
00:02:29,139 --> 00:02:30,300
Way better than your son.

15
00:02:30,900 --> 00:02:32,199
No skills, but plenty of attitude.

16
00:02:33,819 --> 00:02:34,419
Xiaowei, cheers.

17
00:02:34,800 --> 00:02:35,319
My life's pretty much over.

18
00:02:35,319 --> 00:02:36,020
Where are you two going?

19
00:02:46,300 --> 00:02:46,740
Sis,

20
00:02:47,319 --> 00:02:48,979
what if Mom really gives me away?

21
00:02:49,699 --> 00:02:50,400
She won't.

22
00:02:50,960 --> 00:02:52,919
I feel just like that pig.

23
00:02:53,360 --> 00:02:54,199
Live or die,

24
00:02:54,199 --> 00:02:55,659
it's all up to my mom.

25
00:02:56,840 --> 00:02:57,939
Aren't I the same?

26
00:02:58,740 --> 00:03:00,460
Grandma's still in the hospital,

27
00:03:01,139 --> 00:03:02,280
and Mom actually has the nerve

28
00:03:02,319 --> 00:03:03,620
to hook me up with Shu Qingcang.

29
00:03:07,199 --> 00:03:08,919
Don't do what you don't want to do.

30
00:03:09,340 --> 00:03:10,800
Find your own way out.

31
00:03:16,000 --> 00:03:16,580
What a coincidence.

32
00:03:16,840 --> 00:03:18,500
Perfect, let me drive you two back.

33
00:03:23,500 --> 00:03:24,280
Sis,

34
00:03:24,500 --> 00:03:25,199
have you

35
00:03:25,199 --> 00:03:26,300
found your own way out?

36
00:03:27,080 --> 00:03:29,000
A media company in town

37
00:03:29,099 --> 00:03:29,979
sent me a private message.

38
00:03:30,020 --> 00:03:31,099
They want to promote me.

39
00:03:31,900 --> 00:03:32,719
I'm interested.

40
00:03:33,280 --> 00:03:34,039
Might as well give it a shot.

41
00:03:34,960 --> 00:03:36,319
Wait, but you're pregnant.

42
00:03:40,759 --> 00:03:41,900
Don't worry.

43
00:03:41,979 --> 00:03:43,580
I'm feeling great right now.

44
00:03:43,840 --> 00:03:45,719
I don't want to be stuck like this.

45
00:03:46,719 --> 00:03:48,580
It's time we started planning

46
00:03:48,599 --> 00:03:49,560
for our futures.

47
00:03:55,460 --> 00:03:57,560
Rather than let others choose for us,

48
00:03:57,800 --> 00:03:58,900
we should choose for ourselves.

49
00:04:15,960 --> 00:04:17,439
Ms. Yang Fanmei,

50
00:04:18,060 --> 00:04:20,600
By the time you read this letter,

51
00:04:20,800 --> 00:04:22,199
I'll already be gone.

52
00:04:22,779 --> 00:04:23,879
I'm taking my

53
00:04:24,000 --> 00:04:26,079
broken heart

54
00:04:26,500 --> 00:04:28,000
and leaving you forever.

55
00:04:28,660 --> 00:04:30,279
I will use the law

56
00:04:30,459 --> 00:04:31,819
Law

57
00:04:32,360 --> 00:04:33,980
I'll use the weapon of the law

58
00:04:34,279 --> 00:04:36,639
to defend my rights.

59
00:04:36,879 --> 00:04:38,259
I hope when we meet again,

60
00:04:38,339 --> 00:04:40,240
you'll regret everything

61
00:04:40,279 --> 00:04:41,019
you've done!

62
00:04:42,120 --> 00:04:42,759
Fanmei,

63
00:04:43,800 --> 00:04:45,259
Did you hit Dandan again?

64
00:04:45,800 --> 00:04:47,300
Didn't I learn it from you?

65
00:04:48,100 --> 00:04:49,300
Learned from me?

66
00:04:49,360 --> 00:04:51,439
I'm grown up and you still hit me!

67
00:04:51,600 --> 00:04:52,879
Stop, stop hitting me, Mom!

68
00:04:53,300 --> 00:04:54,800
My sister's already not that bright.

69
00:04:56,240 --> 00:04:57,120
Why did Dandan

70
00:04:57,600 --> 00:04:58,600
run away this time?

71
00:04:58,759 --> 00:05:00,019
How would I know?

72
00:05:00,259 --> 00:05:01,540
That little rascal!

73
00:05:01,639 --> 00:05:02,439
There's more here.

74
00:05:02,720 --> 00:05:04,019
This is the last time

75
00:05:04,019 --> 00:05:05,019
I'll ever call you Mom.

76
00:05:05,139 --> 00:05:07,319
Your former son, Qian Zhenqing.

77
00:05:07,720 --> 00:05:08,800
Former son?

78
00:05:09,920 --> 00:05:11,199
Mom, don't worry.

79
00:05:11,279 --> 00:05:12,620
Running away is a path every kid

80
00:05:12,639 --> 00:05:13,879
must take growing up.

81
00:05:13,879 --> 00:05:14,620
We've all been through it.

82
00:05:15,560 --> 00:05:16,399
Nonsense.

83
00:05:16,639 --> 00:05:18,220
Which one of you kids

84
00:05:18,319 --> 00:05:20,019
has ever run away from home?

85
00:05:20,579 --> 00:05:21,579
You just didn't know about it.

86
00:05:21,959 --> 00:05:22,680
I ran away once.

87
00:05:23,439 --> 00:05:24,660
I had no money and got too hungry,

88
00:05:24,839 --> 00:05:26,000
so I came back at dinnertime.

89
00:05:26,019 --> 00:05:26,939
You and Dad never even noticed.

90
00:05:28,019 --> 00:05:29,139
You've got some nerve! Some nerve!

91
00:05:29,139 --> 00:05:30,139
Enough, Mom.

92
00:05:30,620 --> 00:05:31,959
Um, Fanmei,

93
00:05:32,459 --> 00:05:33,879
did Dandan have money on him?

94
00:05:34,800 --> 00:05:35,360
I think so.

95
00:05:35,860 --> 00:05:36,459
That's good then.

96
00:05:37,220 --> 00:05:39,300
That little rascal stole my money!

97
00:05:40,420 --> 00:05:42,160
He's your own son,

98
00:05:42,339 --> 00:05:43,660
and you keep calling him a rascal.

99
00:05:43,839 --> 00:05:45,060
Then what does that make you?

100
00:05:45,579 --> 00:05:46,560
What are you?

101
00:05:46,660 --> 00:05:48,360
What are you still sitting here for?

102
00:05:48,540 --> 00:05:50,040
Why aren't you out looking for him?

103
00:05:50,240 --> 00:05:51,360
My brother went to look.

104
00:05:51,420 --> 00:05:53,600
Don't panic, don't actually get mad.

105
00:05:54,139 --> 00:05:55,839
My brother got Lao Miao,

106
00:05:56,180 --> 00:05:57,879
and they're searching the whole village.

107
00:05:58,240 --> 00:05:58,800
Don't worry.

108
00:06:01,639 --> 00:06:02,759
Where's Xiaofang?

109
00:06:04,540 --> 00:06:05,160
Xiaofang,

110
00:06:05,639 --> 00:06:06,459
are you in your room?

111
00:06:07,319 --> 00:06:08,060
What are you doing?

112
00:06:15,259 --> 00:06:15,740
Mom,

113
00:06:16,959 --> 00:06:17,879
Xiaofang isn't here.

114
00:06:18,860 --> 00:06:19,600
Xiaofang!

115
00:06:20,579 --> 00:06:21,160
Fang!

116
00:06:22,600 --> 00:06:23,360
Xiaofang!

117
00:06:25,680 --> 00:06:26,399
This kid...

118
00:06:27,160 --> 00:06:27,959
With that big belly of hers,

119
00:06:28,019 --> 00:06:28,759
where did she go this time?

120
00:06:31,439 --> 00:06:31,920
Hello?

121
00:06:32,560 --> 00:06:33,480
I'm in the car,

122
00:06:33,519 --> 00:06:34,680
passing Industrial Park Zone 1, Building 10.

123
00:06:35,079 --> 00:06:36,000
Just turn right, then right again.

124
00:06:36,000 --> 00:06:36,579
Right turn.

125
00:06:36,920 --> 00:06:37,920
Let me write it down.

126
00:06:38,100 --> 00:06:40,319
Right, then right again.

127
00:06:40,420 --> 00:06:41,639
Turn, and turn again.

128
00:06:41,879 --> 00:06:42,639
You'll see a bubble tea shop.

129
00:06:42,639 --> 00:06:43,379
What?

130
00:06:44,860 --> 00:06:46,819
Then make a U-turn to the left.

131
00:06:46,819 --> 00:06:47,740
Straight, right turn.

132
00:06:47,800 --> 00:06:48,500
Turn, turn, turn.

133
00:06:48,740 --> 00:06:49,420
Turn what?

134
00:06:49,920 --> 00:06:50,800
Are you driving or am I?

135
00:06:52,259 --> 00:06:53,220
Sorry about that.

136
00:06:54,939 --> 00:06:56,199
Here, we've arrived.

137
00:06:57,660 --> 00:06:58,060
Auntie?

138
00:06:58,060 --> 00:06:58,740
Xiaofang,

139
00:06:59,319 --> 00:07:00,100
where are you?

140
00:07:00,339 --> 00:07:00,800
What are you doing?

141
00:07:00,819 --> 00:07:01,819
Don't push, don't push!

142
00:07:02,740 --> 00:07:04,199
I'm not rushing, not rushing.

143
00:07:04,379 --> 00:07:05,660
Just want to know where you are.

144
00:07:05,660 --> 00:07:06,300
And what you're doing.

145
00:07:06,519 --> 00:07:07,160
Xiaofang!

146
00:07:07,420 --> 00:07:08,759
Are you with Dandan?

147
00:07:09,319 --> 00:07:10,279
Don't, don't touch my belly!

148
00:07:11,160 --> 00:07:12,939
Yes, is Dandan with you?

149
00:07:12,959 --> 00:07:13,939
Is he by your side?

150
00:07:14,139 --> 00:07:15,500
Xiaofang, is he there? Is he?

151
00:07:15,500 --> 00:07:16,399
Yes, yes, yes, he's here.

152
00:07:16,399 --> 00:07:17,259
He's fine, he's fine.

153
00:07:18,839 --> 00:07:19,379
I'm hanging up.

154
00:07:21,100 --> 00:07:21,540
She hung up.

155
00:07:25,480 --> 00:07:27,079
Dandan is with Xiaofang.

156
00:07:27,160 --> 00:07:27,540
Mom,

157
00:07:27,620 --> 00:07:29,120
relax, everything's fine now.

158
00:07:29,540 --> 00:07:30,779
This is when the trouble really starts.

159
00:07:31,000 --> 00:07:31,779
Dandan's still so young,

160
00:07:31,819 --> 00:07:33,040
and he's already running away from home.

161
00:07:33,779 --> 00:07:35,399
That was definitely Xiaofang's idea!

162
00:07:36,160 --> 00:07:36,939
Usually,

163
00:07:37,319 --> 00:07:39,079
when one person runs away,

164
00:07:39,180 --> 00:07:40,139
it's on a whim.

165
00:07:40,139 --> 00:07:41,079
They'll be back soon.

166
00:07:41,500 --> 00:07:43,240
But two together, that's sticking together.

167
00:07:43,540 --> 00:07:44,399
They probably won't be back till tomorrow.

168
00:07:44,579 --> 00:07:45,399
You shut up.

169
00:07:45,579 --> 00:07:46,699
Stirring up trouble all day.

170
00:07:47,680 --> 00:07:48,339
What are you doing?

171
00:07:50,019 --> 00:07:50,680
Stop worrying.

172
00:08:00,439 --> 00:08:02,019
Driver, drive steadily, will you?

173
00:08:18,500 --> 00:08:19,879
Yang Xiaofang, just wait till you get back.

174
00:08:20,459 --> 00:08:21,500
See how I'll deal with you.

175
00:08:22,220 --> 00:08:23,899
A bad workman blames his tools.

176
00:08:24,360 --> 00:08:25,620
Can't handle your own kid,

177
00:08:25,899 --> 00:08:26,819
so you blame others.

178
00:08:27,480 --> 00:08:27,740
How am I...

179
00:08:27,740 --> 00:08:29,019
Where did Xiaofang go?

180
00:08:29,040 --> 00:08:30,660
It sounded chaotic on the phone just now.

181
00:08:30,680 --> 00:08:31,720
Yeah, total chaos.

182
00:08:32,159 --> 00:08:32,559
Fanmei.

183
00:08:33,120 --> 00:08:34,500
Try calling Dandan again.

184
00:08:35,019 --> 00:08:35,980
That little rascal.

185
00:08:36,080 --> 00:08:36,419
You...

186
00:08:37,899 --> 00:08:38,980
The kid blocked me.

187
00:08:42,980 --> 00:08:44,220
Unknown number. Who is it?

188
00:08:45,860 --> 00:08:46,580
Hello, who's this?

189
00:08:47,039 --> 00:08:47,820
Yang Fanyan.

190
00:08:48,279 --> 00:08:49,139
Look what you've done.

191
00:08:49,960 --> 00:08:50,639
Zhi Qiang.

192
00:08:51,019 --> 00:08:51,759
What's the matter?

193
00:08:51,940 --> 00:08:52,980
Jingjing won't take my calls.

194
00:08:52,980 --> 00:08:53,779
She even blocked me.

195
00:08:53,879 --> 00:08:54,940
She won't take your calls,

196
00:08:55,000 --> 00:08:55,580
she blocked you,

197
00:08:55,600 --> 00:08:56,700
what's that got to do with me?

198
00:08:57,240 --> 00:08:58,480
Did you set her up on a blind date?

199
00:08:59,039 --> 00:09:00,259
When we divorced, you didn't want the kid.

200
00:09:00,519 --> 00:09:02,320
Now she's grown, and suddenly you care?

201
00:09:02,779 --> 00:09:04,100
Trying to find someone to support you in old age,

202
00:09:04,120 --> 00:09:04,580
huh?

203
00:09:04,679 --> 00:09:05,919
Let me tell you, it's no use.

204
00:09:06,379 --> 00:09:07,100
You didn't care before,

205
00:09:07,200 --> 00:09:08,340
don't expect any benefits later.

206
00:09:08,720 --> 00:09:09,580
I didn't care before?

207
00:09:09,679 --> 00:09:10,740
I did plenty.

208
00:09:11,200 --> 00:09:12,100
Her monthly allowance,

209
00:09:12,100 --> 00:09:13,019
did I ever shortchange her?

210
00:09:13,240 --> 00:09:14,299
Holiday red envelopes,

211
00:09:14,379 --> 00:09:15,340
did I ever miss one?

212
00:09:16,080 --> 00:09:17,240
Her clothes, her things,

213
00:09:17,419 --> 00:09:18,539
which weren't paid for with my money?

214
00:09:18,720 --> 00:09:20,059
Fine, I'll make a list

215
00:09:20,139 --> 00:09:21,039
and have Jingjing pay you back.

216
00:09:21,100 --> 00:09:22,100
You, you...

217
00:09:24,940 --> 00:09:26,120
This is outrageous!

218
00:09:28,480 --> 00:09:29,240
What are you all staring at?

219
00:09:31,159 --> 00:09:31,940
So unreasonable.

220
00:09:34,740 --> 00:09:35,220
Sis.

221
00:09:35,919 --> 00:09:36,899
Jingjing blocked her dad.

222
00:09:36,919 --> 00:09:37,799
Try calling her yourself.

223
00:09:45,559 --> 00:09:46,220
Hello,

224
00:09:46,340 --> 00:09:47,340
the number you have dialed

225
00:09:47,340 --> 00:09:48,500
is currently busy.

226
00:09:48,539 --> 00:09:49,139
Please try again later.

227
00:09:49,200 --> 00:09:49,600
Busy.

228
00:09:49,799 --> 00:09:50,720
She blocked you too.

229
00:09:54,899 --> 00:09:56,820
She couldn't have blocked me on WeChat, right?

230
00:09:58,100 --> 00:09:59,960
The other party hasn't added you as a friend,

231
00:10:00,220 --> 00:10:01,460
so voice calls aren't allowed.

232
00:10:04,220 --> 00:10:05,620
I mean, so early in the morning,

233
00:10:06,080 --> 00:10:07,019
these three kids...

234
00:10:07,500 --> 00:10:09,000
This is totally absurd,

235
00:10:09,179 --> 00:10:10,879
it's just bizarre.

236
00:10:12,940 --> 00:10:14,000
I get it now, Sis.

237
00:10:15,179 --> 00:10:17,080
Xiaofang, Dandan, Jingjing,

238
00:10:17,200 --> 00:10:19,019
all three vanished at once.

239
00:10:19,080 --> 00:10:20,539
Think about it, this isn't just

240
00:10:20,559 --> 00:10:21,919
a simple case of running away from home.

241
00:10:21,919 --> 00:10:22,399
Just think...

242
00:10:22,620 --> 00:10:23,600
Enough, stop keeping us in suspense.

243
00:10:23,620 --> 00:10:24,139
Just spit it out.

244
00:10:24,299 --> 00:10:25,539
Here's my reasonable deduction.

245
00:10:26,200 --> 00:10:27,899
One person is a coincidence,

246
00:10:28,320 --> 00:10:30,519
two people is a fluke,

247
00:10:33,360 --> 00:10:34,460
but three people

248
00:10:34,820 --> 00:10:35,840
disappearing together?

249
00:10:37,519 --> 00:10:38,399
Isn't this a

250
00:10:39,799 --> 00:10:42,000
premeditated group operation?

251
00:10:42,220 --> 00:10:43,220
Just my guess, just guessing.

252
00:10:43,279 --> 00:10:44,279
You'd better make yourself clear.

253
00:10:44,620 --> 00:10:45,960
Are you really in the dark about this?

254
00:10:46,399 --> 00:10:47,299
Talk, now.

255
00:10:58,620 --> 00:10:59,820
Yeah, what's going on here?

256
00:11:00,220 --> 00:11:01,200
I heard Xiaofang ran off.

257
00:11:01,740 --> 00:11:02,440
Can't be found anywhere.

258
00:11:03,720 --> 00:11:04,639
Did she run off with...

259
00:11:04,679 --> 00:11:05,539
that Shu Qingcang?

260
00:11:06,279 --> 00:11:07,080
No, that wouldn't happen.

261
00:11:08,200 --> 00:11:08,960
Xiaowei told me

262
00:11:09,019 --> 00:11:10,200
the Yang family is quite pleased

263
00:11:10,240 --> 00:11:10,820
with that Shu guy.

264
00:11:10,940 --> 00:11:12,519
She wouldn't run off with him of all people.

265
00:11:15,679 --> 00:11:16,299
Xiaowei!

266
00:11:18,720 --> 00:11:19,299
Xiaowei!

267
00:11:21,059 --> 00:11:21,480
Xiaowei!

268
00:11:22,399 --> 00:11:23,720
Stop sleeping, get up now!

269
00:11:23,759 --> 00:11:24,639
Get up, get up, something's happened!

270
00:11:24,840 --> 00:11:26,200
Look at the time, hurry up!

271
00:11:28,919 --> 00:11:29,559
Oh my God.

272
00:11:30,220 --> 00:11:31,360
I didn't see him leave.

273
00:11:32,980 --> 00:11:33,299
What the...

274
00:11:34,279 --> 00:11:34,639
This...

275
00:11:38,240 --> 00:11:38,940
No way.

276
00:11:42,080 --> 00:11:42,940
Where on earth could

277
00:11:42,960 --> 00:11:43,840
these three kids have gone?

278
00:11:44,100 --> 00:11:44,820
Following Xiaofang,

279
00:11:44,840 --> 00:11:45,519
they could be anywhere.

280
00:11:45,519 --> 00:11:46,419
Back then, my plan was

281
00:11:46,460 --> 00:11:47,220
Shanghai first, then Beijing,

282
00:11:47,220 --> 00:11:48,259
and then head abroad, I'd...

283
00:11:48,340 --> 00:11:49,440
Why don't you just fly to the moon?

284
00:11:49,519 --> 00:11:51,039
Mom, you can't just say things like that.

285
00:11:52,340 --> 00:11:53,759
Didn't you say Dandan was missing?

286
00:11:54,620 --> 00:11:55,440
Xiaofang and Jingjing,

287
00:11:55,460 --> 00:11:56,659
