00:28:42,480 --> 00:28:43,599
So basically, make up stories.

865
00:28:43,680 --> 00:28:44,460
Quick learner!

866
00:28:44,960 --> 00:28:45,519
Hey kid,

867
00:28:46,359 --> 00:28:47,700
I understand your troubles.

868
00:28:48,180 --> 00:28:48,940
But,

869
00:28:49,380 --> 00:28:50,299
you're a minor.

870
00:28:50,599 --> 00:28:52,519
I need to take you back to your parents first.

871
00:28:52,680 --> 00:28:53,319
Got it?

872
00:28:53,960 --> 00:28:55,480
Come on, let's take him to...

873
00:28:56,700 --> 00:28:56,960
Hey!

874
00:28:56,960 --> 00:28:58,079
Why'd he crawl under the table?

875
00:28:58,359 --> 00:28:59,539
Hurry, get him out!

876
00:28:59,680 --> 00:29:00,279
That's so dangerous!

877
00:29:00,680 --> 00:29:01,440
Come out, come out.

878
00:29:02,740 --> 00:29:03,259
Kid!

879
00:29:03,960 --> 00:29:04,980
What are you doing to my leg?

880
00:29:05,559 --> 00:29:06,119
Come on out.

881
00:29:06,519 --> 00:29:07,579
Stop tugging on it!

882
00:29:07,660 --> 00:29:08,359
Help!

883
00:29:09,519 --> 00:29:10,619
I've already got the debut theme figured out.

884
00:29:11,319 --> 00:29:12,339
We'll call it this:

885
00:29:12,559 --> 00:29:14,519
"Women may be weak,

886
00:29:15,099 --> 00:29:16,579
but mothers are strong."

887
00:29:17,000 --> 00:29:17,759
When the time comes, you play up

888
00:29:17,779 --> 00:29:18,920
your single-mom identity.

889
00:29:19,019 --> 00:29:19,740
Milk the sob story hard.

890
00:29:19,960 --> 00:29:21,480
There's huge potential!

891
00:29:21,920 --> 00:29:23,460
What's so sad about being single with a kid?

892
00:29:26,059 --> 00:29:28,940
Not actually sad, just fake it!

893
00:29:33,500 --> 00:29:34,779
Don't be in such a rush to leave.

894
00:29:36,059 --> 00:29:36,799
People like you,

895
00:29:36,839 --> 00:29:37,559
I've seen plenty of.

896
00:29:37,819 --> 00:29:38,700
The moment you get a bit of traffic,

897
00:29:38,700 --> 00:29:39,640
you think you're a big deal.

898
00:29:39,880 --> 00:29:40,839
But let me tell you,

899
00:29:40,960 --> 00:29:42,799
this world has its own rules.

900
00:29:42,799 --> 00:29:43,319
You get it?

901
00:29:47,420 --> 00:29:48,779
I'm only saying this because you've got potential.

902
00:29:49,380 --> 00:29:50,440
So I'll spell it out for you.

903
00:29:51,000 --> 00:29:51,799
If you wanna make money,

904
00:29:52,539 --> 00:29:54,000
don't treat yourself like a human,

905
00:29:54,460 --> 00:29:55,720
and don't treat others like humans either.

906
00:29:56,220 --> 00:29:57,519
Get the money in your hands first.

907
00:29:57,640 --> 00:29:58,119
Am I right?

908
00:29:58,380 --> 00:29:59,799
Everyone does it this way.

909
00:30:00,259 --> 00:30:01,720
Who are you to be the exception?

910
00:30:07,579 --> 00:30:08,539
I'm not the exception.

911
00:30:09,380 --> 00:30:10,400
And don't feel inferior, okay?

912
00:30:13,859 --> 00:30:14,339
Me?

913
00:30:15,059 --> 00:30:15,700
Me?

914
00:30:15,839 --> 00:30:16,880
Me, feel inferior?

915
00:30:17,500 --> 00:30:18,660
What do I have to feel inferior about?

916
00:30:18,759 --> 00:30:19,960
I run such a big company.

917
00:30:20,579 --> 00:30:22,500
Sooner or later, you'll crawl back begging me.

918
00:30:22,599 --> 00:30:24,920
I'm telling you, your words are too hurtful.

919
00:30:24,920 --> 00:30:26,619
How can you be like this?

920
00:30:27,059 --> 00:30:28,140
Me, inferior?

921
00:30:28,960 --> 00:30:29,779
Me, inferior?

922
00:30:30,180 --> 00:30:32,519
Do I, do I look inferior to you?

923
00:30:47,720 --> 00:30:48,440
Where's my phone?

924
00:30:51,420 --> 00:30:52,140
My phone.

925
00:30:59,099 --> 00:31:01,200
I'm all flustered right now.

926
00:31:04,680 --> 00:31:05,900
I livestreamed with it for a week.

927
00:31:05,900 --> 00:31:07,220
Now I stink all over.

928
00:31:07,319 --> 00:31:08,400
Just looking at it annoys me.

929
00:31:08,640 --> 00:31:10,099
Relax, once we finish filming, it's gone.

930
00:31:10,160 --> 00:31:10,680
We'll just sell it.

931
00:31:10,940 --> 00:31:11,700
You won't have to see it again.

932
00:31:12,180 --> 00:31:13,079
That useless thing.

933
00:31:13,079 --> 00:31:14,400
Why bother keeping it?

934
00:31:14,720 --> 00:31:16,819
I want it gone, right now.

935
00:31:16,880 --> 00:31:17,599
You hear me?

936
00:31:22,779 --> 00:31:23,440
I'm really busy.

937
00:31:23,539 --> 00:31:24,440
I can't find a buyer for it.

938
00:31:24,819 --> 00:31:25,920
I've got my own work to do.

939
00:31:26,279 --> 00:31:26,880
Besides,

940
00:31:26,940 --> 00:31:28,240
who'd want to buy such an old cow?

941
00:31:28,839 --> 00:31:29,160
Forget it.

942
00:31:29,539 --> 00:31:30,359
We've got a flight to catch.

943
00:31:30,420 --> 00:31:31,019
Let's just go.

944
00:32:20,980 --> 00:32:22,099
You borrow money, you spend it

945
00:32:22,140 --> 00:32:23,460
Why must you tell the family?

946
00:32:23,619 --> 00:32:24,140
Seriously

947
00:32:24,140 --> 00:32:25,240
Just say so if you won't lend it

948
00:32:25,920 --> 00:32:26,539
Jingjing

949
00:32:27,460 --> 00:32:27,960
Xiaofang

950
00:32:28,759 --> 00:32:30,440
This town is way too small

951
00:32:31,440 --> 00:32:33,079
Where'd you even get a cow?

952
00:32:33,660 --> 00:32:35,319
It... it got laid off.

953
00:32:36,480 --> 00:32:38,640
Help! Help! Help!

954
00:32:38,859 --> 00:32:39,819
Dandan

955
00:32:40,359 --> 00:32:41,359
They're bullying me

956
00:32:41,720 --> 00:32:42,400
What's going on?

957
00:32:42,900 --> 00:32:43,700
Why are you here?

958
00:32:44,039 --> 00:32:45,079
They're bullying me

959
00:32:45,119 --> 00:32:46,400
I came to report my mom

960
00:32:49,319 --> 00:32:49,660
Look

961
00:32:49,960 --> 00:32:51,059
Your sis got you a cow

962
00:32:56,099 --> 00:32:56,680
Dandan

963
00:32:58,119 --> 00:32:58,980
Mom was wrong

964
00:33:01,119 --> 00:33:02,299
I shouldn't have said I'd

965
00:33:02,420 --> 00:33:03,680
give you to Grand Uncle.

966
00:33:04,940 --> 00:33:05,279
Second Sis

967
00:33:05,359 --> 00:33:07,259
Why would you give Dandan away?

968
00:33:08,579 --> 00:33:09,619
Uncle wants the baby

969
00:33:09,640 --> 00:33:10,839
in Xiaofang's belly.

970
00:33:11,619 --> 00:33:12,640
Xiaofang won't agree

971
00:33:13,420 --> 00:33:14,019
So I thought

972
00:33:14,880 --> 00:33:16,380
Dandan is also a boy

973
00:33:17,259 --> 00:33:17,539
And

974
00:33:17,900 --> 00:33:19,539
Uncle's family is well-off.

975
00:33:19,960 --> 00:33:21,140
Uncle wants the baby

976
00:33:21,240 --> 00:33:22,440
in Xiaofang's belly

977
00:33:22,500 --> 00:33:23,859
Who said that?

978
00:33:23,859 --> 00:33:25,000
When did this happen?

979
00:33:25,839 --> 00:33:26,799
Are you really that clueless

980
00:33:26,839 --> 00:33:27,839
or just pretending?

981
00:33:28,440 --> 00:33:29,400
Uncle hasn't contacted us

982
00:33:29,440 --> 00:33:30,680
for so many years

983
00:33:30,900 --> 00:33:33,220
Suddenly treating us, giving red envelopes

984
00:33:33,559 --> 00:33:34,519
What's he after?

985
00:33:34,960 --> 00:33:35,940
Isn't it all for that boy

986
00:33:35,980 --> 00:33:38,059
in Xiaofang's belly?

987
00:33:39,140 --> 00:33:40,000
Big Sis, if you knew

988
00:33:40,000 --> 00:33:41,460
why didn't you tell us?

989
00:33:41,880 --> 00:33:43,000
She thinks she can handle it

990
00:33:44,160 --> 00:33:45,579
Like we're all fools and idiots

991
00:33:46,119 --> 00:33:47,160
She knew exactly what Shu Qingcang

992
00:33:47,160 --> 00:33:48,099
was scheming

993
00:33:48,599 --> 00:33:49,859
Yet she forced Xiaofang to date him

994
00:33:50,119 --> 00:33:51,519
She's the one who drove Xiaofang away

995
00:33:52,180 --> 00:33:53,920
Jingjing's grandma is dying

996
00:33:54,579 --> 00:33:55,400
And at a time like this

997
00:33:55,819 --> 00:33:57,720
she pushes her to meet Shu Qingcang.

998
00:33:58,099 --> 00:33:58,960
Yang Fanyan

999
00:34:00,059 --> 00:34:00,940
If I were Jingjing

1000
00:34:00,980 --> 00:34:02,259
I wouldn't call you my mother

1001
00:34:06,440 --> 00:34:06,900
Fine

1002
00:34:09,059 --> 00:34:09,940
It's all my fault

1003
00:34:11,860 --> 00:34:12,619
All these years

1004
00:34:13,460 --> 00:34:15,179
I've toiled and sacrificed for this family

1005
00:34:16,039 --> 00:34:17,440
Thinking of each and every one of you

1006
00:34:17,780 --> 00:34:19,480
I was wrong, okay?

1007
00:34:19,760 --> 00:34:21,480
It's all my fault, alright?

1008
00:34:23,539 --> 00:34:24,539
If my life could buy back

1009
00:34:24,619 --> 00:34:26,280
the safety of my three children

1010
00:34:26,500 --> 00:34:27,900
I'd take it. I was wrong

1011
00:34:28,019 --> 00:34:28,900
Okay?

1012
00:34:53,079 --> 00:34:53,619
Dandan

1013
00:34:53,679 --> 00:34:54,500
After you finish eating

1014
00:34:54,599 --> 00:34:55,599
give your mom a call

1015
00:34:55,699 --> 00:34:56,800
She must be worried

1016
00:34:57,599 --> 00:34:58,199
I'm not calling

1017
00:34:58,360 --> 00:34:59,139
Let her worry

1018
00:34:59,780 --> 00:35:01,039
She's the one who wanted to give me away.

1019
00:35:03,099 --> 00:35:04,119
Fine, then eat first

1020
00:35:04,239 --> 00:35:05,179
Call her a bit later, okay?

1021
00:35:06,800 --> 00:35:08,000
I came to borrow money

1022
00:35:08,099 --> 00:35:09,639
Didn't get a single cent

1023
00:35:11,139 --> 00:35:12,440
I came to find a job

1024
00:35:12,599 --> 00:35:13,820
No job found

1025
00:35:13,900 --> 00:35:14,920
Lost my phone

1026
00:35:15,420 --> 00:35:16,460
Picked up this little guy

1027
00:35:17,840 --> 00:35:18,920
I came to sue my mom

1028
00:35:19,159 --> 00:35:20,099
Lawsuit fell through

1029
00:35:20,360 --> 00:35:21,219
Ate a burger

1030
00:35:27,639 --> 00:35:28,840
With him along

1031
00:35:29,980 --> 00:35:31,000
how are we gonna catch a ride?

1032
00:35:32,960 --> 00:35:33,519
Yeah, right

1033
00:35:34,000 --> 00:35:34,360
This...

1034
00:35:34,800 --> 00:35:36,139
No one will take us

1035
00:35:36,159 --> 00:35:36,480
Then...

1036
00:35:36,900 --> 00:35:38,360
Then we'll walk back without a ride

1037
00:35:38,659 --> 00:35:39,639
When would we ever get there?

1038
00:35:40,719 --> 00:35:42,239
Didn't you run away from home?

1039
00:35:42,340 --> 00:35:43,719
What, in a rush to go home now?

1040
00:35:44,480 --> 00:35:45,340
Who wants to see Yang Fanmei?

1041
00:35:45,340 --> 00:35:46,260
I just want to sleep

1042
00:35:46,500 --> 00:35:47,659
Just eat your burger

1043
00:35:51,519 --> 00:35:52,139
Boss

1044
00:35:53,199 --> 00:35:53,800
Um...

1045
00:35:53,940 --> 00:35:55,639
Are you using this cart right now?

1046
00:35:55,699 --> 00:35:56,519
Could you lend it to us?

1047
00:35:56,659 --> 00:35:57,480
We'll give you a deposit.

1048
00:35:57,519 --> 00:35:58,639
We'll return it in a couple of days.

1049
00:35:58,980 --> 00:36:00,139
I'm leaving in a few days.

1050
00:36:00,360 --> 00:36:01,400
I won't need this cart anymore.

1051
00:36:01,539 --> 00:36:03,280
If you want it, take it for fifty yuan.

1052
00:36:03,719 --> 00:36:04,159
Thank you.

1053
00:36:04,559 --> 00:36:05,059
Problem solved.

1054
00:36:05,400 --> 00:36:06,099
Boss.

1055
00:36:06,539 --> 00:36:07,780
Are you transferring this shop?

1056
00:36:08,920 --> 00:36:10,659
Actually, I'm just staying here as a traveler.

1057
00:36:10,960 --> 00:36:12,199
I've experienced this place enough.

1058
00:36:12,340 --> 00:36:13,000
Next month,

1059
00:36:13,079 --> 00:36:14,139
I'm heading to my next stop.

1060
00:36:14,300 --> 00:36:15,380
Wow, so cool!

1061
00:36:15,380 --> 00:36:16,500
This shop of yours,

1062
00:36:17,059 --> 00:36:17,679
does it make money?

1063
00:36:18,380 --> 00:36:19,559
It definitely makes money.

1064
00:36:19,820 --> 00:36:20,699
There are lots of my regulars

1065
00:36:20,739 --> 00:36:21,559
around here.

1066
00:36:21,659 --> 00:36:23,099
Whoever takes over won't have to worry.

1067
00:36:26,079 --> 00:36:27,340
I'm not going back to Guangdong to work.

1068
00:36:28,599 --> 00:36:30,219
I plan to stay in the county town.

1069
00:36:30,219 --> 00:36:31,599
Find a job and stay with Grandma.

1070
00:36:32,539 --> 00:36:33,179
Xiaofang.

1071
00:36:33,360 --> 00:36:34,119
You were right.

1072
00:36:34,760 --> 00:36:35,599
Live in the moment.

1073
00:36:36,420 --> 00:36:37,679
What I can do right now

1074
00:36:38,099 --> 00:36:39,679
is for every day Grandma's in the hospital,

1075
00:36:39,800 --> 00:36:40,780
I'll spend one more day with her.

1076
00:36:41,780 --> 00:36:43,880
As for the rest, I'll take it one step at a time.

1077
00:36:44,420 --> 00:36:44,739
Right.

1078
00:36:47,039 --> 00:36:48,400
I even learned to do nails before.

1079
00:36:48,760 --> 00:36:50,340
Maybe someday when I make money,

1080
00:36:50,500 --> 00:36:52,179
I could open my own nail salon.

1081
00:36:53,099 --> 00:36:53,679
Jingjing.

1082
00:36:53,960 --> 00:36:54,619
Haven't you always

1083
00:36:54,619 --> 00:36:55,760
wanted to open a nail salon?

1084
00:36:59,380 --> 00:37:00,639
Isn't this perfect?

1085
00:37:01,260 --> 00:37:02,119
I'm in a hurry to leave.

1086
00:37:02,239 --> 00:37:03,199
If you take it over,

1087
00:37:03,579 --> 00:37:04,179
I'll

1088
00:37:04,760 --> 00:37:06,019
give you an extra 20% off.

1089
00:37:06,539 --> 00:37:07,460
The shop has everything.

1090
00:37:07,760 --> 00:37:09,280
Pay today, open for business tomorrow.

1091
00:37:09,840 --> 00:37:10,579
Then how about

1092
00:37:11,079 --> 00:37:12,159
we don't be employees anymore

1093
00:37:12,639 --> 00:37:13,420
and just be our own bosses?

1094
00:37:14,260 --> 00:37:15,139
Isn't that too hasty?

1095
00:37:15,579 --> 00:37:16,579
Then I'll buy in as a shareholder.

1096
00:37:17,300 --> 00:37:18,360
I'll start from scratch,

1097
00:37:18,599 --> 00:37:20,159
run a business like Lao Qian and make big money.

1098
00:37:20,219 --> 00:37:21,019
Help Lao Qian pay off his debts.

1099
00:37:21,960 --> 00:37:22,480
Can't I?

1100
00:37:22,880 --> 00:37:23,420
Will it work?

1101
00:37:23,820 --> 00:37:24,340
Let's give it a try.

1102
00:37:27,199 --> 00:37:28,179
Even it says it'll work.

1103
00:37:28,460 --> 00:37:29,539
If it says yes, then I say yes too.

1104
00:37:29,559 --> 00:37:30,599
If it says it works, it works.

1105
00:37:34,360 --> 00:37:35,179
I've got it all figured out.

1106
00:37:35,179 --> 00:37:36,579
I want to make a drinks bar.

1107
00:37:36,800 --> 00:37:38,400
I can make coffee,

1108
00:37:38,579 --> 00:37:39,920
I can make coconut candy.

1109
00:37:40,000 --> 00:37:42,019
I don't know if people around here

1110
00:37:42,019 --> 00:37:43,000
like drinking this kind of stuff.

1111
00:37:43,000 --> 00:37:43,619
So I...

1112
00:37:44,159 --> 00:37:45,239
What do you think?

1113
00:37:45,380 --> 00:37:46,300
Give me some suggestions.

1114
00:37:46,780 --> 00:37:48,099
Your idea sounds great.

1115
00:37:48,400 --> 00:37:49,639
Let's go back and plan it out.

1116
00:37:57,760 --> 00:37:59,000
What kind of mess is this?

1117
00:38:01,679 --> 00:38:02,840
It was all a big mix-up.

1118
00:38:05,980 --> 00:38:06,639
It's all your fault.

1119
00:38:06,699 --> 00:38:08,139
Watching movies rotted your brain.

1120
00:38:08,500 --> 00:38:09,579
You were the one who took it seriously first!

1121
00:38:09,579 --> 00:38:10,519
And now you're blaming me?

1122
00:38:10,519 --> 00:38:11,280
Me, serious?

1123
00:38:11,380 --> 00:38:11,900
You... you...

1124
00:38:13,059 --> 00:38:14,179
Where do you think Xiaofang and them

1125
00:38:14,239 --> 00:38:15,139
could be right now?

1126
00:38:18,219 --> 00:38:19,139
My guess is

1127
00:38:19,980 --> 00:38:21,099
they're not coming home.

1128
00:38:23,019 --> 00:38:23,659
Let's head back too.

1129
00:38:24,159 --> 00:38:24,559
Go home.

1130
00:38:38,960 --> 00:38:39,500
What's wrong?

1131
00:38:39,780 --> 00:38:40,280
What happened?

1132
00:38:41,440 --> 00:38:42,059
We're out of gas.

1133
00:38:48,739 --> 00:38:49,460
Can you two handle this?

1134
00:38:49,639 --> 00:38:50,099
It's fine.

1135
00:38:51,559 --> 00:38:52,519
I just checked the GPS.

1136
00:38:52,860 --> 00:38:53,679
The nearest gas station

1137
00:38:53,679 --> 00:38:54,579
is ten kilometers away.

1138
00:38:54,920 --> 00:38:55,920
Ten kilometers?

1139
00:38:55,960 --> 00:38:57,699
Before the weather cools, we're done for.

1140
00:38:59,099 --> 00:39:00,199
We'd better find someone

1141
00:39:00,280 --> 00:39:01,639
to bring us some gas.

1142
00:39:02,480 --> 00:39:03,480
Who's gonna bring it?

1143
00:39:04,320 --> 00:39:04,940
Look.

1144
00:39:04,940 --> 00:39:06,519
It's not gonna rain soon, is it?

1145
00:39:06,739 --> 00:39:07,480
No way.

1146
00:39:07,860 --> 00:39:08,460
Then what?

1147
00:39:08,500 --> 00:39:09,340
We'd better hurry.

1148
00:39:09,340 --> 00:39:10,519
What if it starts raining?

1149
00:39:10,539 --> 00:39:11,059
Dandan!

1150
00:39:11,099 --> 00:39:11,659
Okay, hurry.

1151
00:39:12,500 --> 00:39:13,219
No rain yet.

1152
00:39:19,519 --> 00:39:20,159
Dandan!

1153
00:39:20,920 --> 00:39:21,380
Sis!

1154
00:39:21,400 --> 00:39:21,860
Slow down, slow down.

1155
00:39:21,860 --> 00:39:22,500
Look, everyone.

1156
00:39:26,260 --> 00:39:26,880
Dad!

1157
00:39:29,159 --> 00:39:29,699
Jingjing!

1158
00:39:29,699 --> 00:39:30,219
Stop, stop, stop!

1159
00:39:30,519 --> 00:39:31,480
Dandan, hurry, hurry!

1160
00:39:32,980 --> 00:39:34,059
Dandan!

1161
00:39:34,199 --> 00:39:34,800
Mom!

1162
00:39:37,300 --> 00:39:38,739
You scared me to death.

1163
00:39:39,280 --> 00:39:40,340
Why are they here?

1164
00:39:42,360 --> 00:39:42,840
Mom.

1165
00:39:51,820 --> 00:39:52,539
Are you okay?

1166
00:39:56,099 --> 00:39:57,059
You came looking for me!

1167
00:40:03,440 --> 00:40:04,519
You're drenched in sweat.

1168
00:40:18,980 --> 00:40:19,599
Son.

1169
00:40:21,019 --> 00:40:22,019
I'm so sorry.

1170
00:40:22,599 --> 00:40:24,079
Mom never once wanted

1171
00:40:24,320 --> 00:40:25,019
to give you away.

1172
00:40:25,619 --> 00:40:26,800
Mommy was wrong.

1173
00:40:27,780 --> 00:40:28,619
You scared me to death.

1174
00:40:29,500 --> 00:40:30,400
What happened?

1175
00:40:31,300 --> 00:40:32,179
I thought you guys

1176
00:40:33,300 --> 00:40:34,239
had been kidnapped.

1177
00:40:47,920 --> 00:40:49,239
I'm sorry.

1178
00:41:01,639 --> 00:41:02,619
I didn't see anything.

1179
00:41:02,780 --> 00:41:04,039
I didn't see a thing.

1180
00:41:08,239 --> 00:41:09,699
Good thing you're here, Brother Ox.

1181
00:41:11,539 --> 00:41:12,659
Guess we'll just make do together.

1182
00:41:14,019 --> 00:41:15,099
Your car broke down?

1183
00:41:16,820 --> 00:41:17,440
It's out of gas.

1184
00:41:48,820 --> 00:41:50,340
I want to file a complaint against my mother.

1185
00:41:51,059 --> 00:41:52,139
She may have given birth to me,

1186
00:41:52,699 --> 00:41:53,519
and raised me,

1187
00:41:54,019 --> 00:41:55,300
but she neither understands me,

1188
00:41:55,840 --> 00:41:56,719
nor respects me.

1189
00:41:57,159 --> 00:41:58,780
She always says I don't know a damn thing.

1190
00:41:59,179 --> 00:42:00,360
I want to grow up fast,

1191
00:42:01,119 --> 00:42:02,800
because only when you're an adult

1192
00:42:03,019 --> 00:42:04,300
do your words carry any weight,

1193
00:42:05,260 --> 00:42:06,539
and only then can you be respected.

1194
00:42:07,360 --> 00:42:08,440
I want to tell my mom,

1195
00:42:08,739 --> 00:42:09,980
I'm not some clueless

1196
00:42:10,039 --> 00:42:10,760
little brat.

1197
00:42:11,320 --> 00:42:12,019
And I'm not some object

1198
00:42:12,039 --> 00:42:13,420
she can just give away to anyone.

1199
00:42:14,000 --> 00:42:15,280
This time, I'm not the one in the wrong.

1200
00:42:15,719 --> 00:42:16,239
She is.

1201
00:42:21,639 --> 00:42:23,039
Blow a big one!

1202
00:42:28,980 --> 00:42:29,760
Look at them.

1203
00:42:31,119 --> 00:42:33,139
These kids, they've all grown up.

1204
00:42:34,860 --> 00:42:36,760
It's time to let them go.

1205
00:43:04,579 --> 00:43:05,860
Actually, it's them

1206
00:43:07,019 --> 00:43:09,000
who are pulling us forward.

1207
00:43:23,539 --> 00:43:23,960
Mom

1208
00:43:24,239 --> 00:43:25,860
I really want to go study painting.

1209
00:43:25,860 --> 00:43:27,519
I don't want to follow my brother into

1210
00:43:27,519 --> 00:43:28,360
that construction work.

1211
00:43:28,440 --> 00:43:29,579
Mom supports you.

1212
00:43:29,880 --> 00:43:30,900
Mom has a little stash

1213
00:43:31,380 --> 00:43:32,300
of cash.

1214
00:43:34,519 --> 00:43:35,900
Lao Qitou!

1215
00:43:36,860 --> 00:43:38,039
Where's my money?

1216
00:43:40,280 --> 00:43:41,820
Trying to mess with me?

1217
00:43:42,119 --> 00:43:42,679
Let's work hard.

1218
00:43:42,820 --> 00:43:44,360
Work hard to prove we don't need

1219
00:43:44,360 --> 00:43:45,539
them making decisions for us.

1220
00:43:45,880 --> 00:43:46,619
But right now,

1221
00:43:46,619 --> 00:43:47,699
we can't even scrape together the money.

1222
00:43:47,719 --> 00:43:48,719
We can find outside help.

1223
00:43:50,199 --> 00:43:50,760
Who?

1224
00:43:51,659 --> 00:43:53,119
Take them down one by one.

